#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.86"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.86:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.86:0.2"
msgid "9. Channavagga"
msgstr "9. With Channa"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 86. Saṅkhittadhammasutta → saṅkhitta (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.86:0.3"
msgid "86. Saṅkhittadhammasutta"
msgstr "86. A Teaching In Brief"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:1.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated to one side, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn35.86:1.2"
msgid ""
"“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato "
"dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’"
"ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:2.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, ānanda, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Ānanda? "

msgctxt "sn35.86:2.2"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:3.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:4.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:5.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to "
"be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn35.86:6.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:7.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:8.1"
msgid "“Rūpā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Are sights …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:9.1"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante” … pe …."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.55"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:10.1"
msgid "“Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "eye consciousness … eye contact …"

msgctxt "sn35.86:10.2"
msgid ""
"yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye "
"contact: is that permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.86:11.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
